{
  "texts": [
    "This is particularly relevant to olfactory signal processing, where the intricate chemical nature of odorants necessitates advanced modeling techniques for decoding high-dimensional characteristics.",
    "Such methodologies enhance the accuracy and efficiency of olfactory analysis systems, such as electronic noses, which depend on precise representations of molecular data.",
    "Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) have emerged as powerful tools for analyzing spatial and temporal patterns in olfactory data, effectively capturing spatial correlations between sensors and the dynamic responses to gas exposure (Ni et al. 2024).",
    "Additionally, Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) and Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks are particularly suited for modeling the temporal dependencies inherent in olfactory data (Xing et al. 2022).",
    "These models excel at tracking changing odor signals, making them ideal for real-time applications such as air quality monitoring and industrial leak detection."
  ]
}